---
description: Conventional Commits guidance for this repository
alwaysApply: false
---

- Use Conventional Commits: `feat`, `fix`, `refactor`, `docs`, `test`, `chore`, `perf`, `build`, `ci`.
- Format: `type(scope)!: short summary` (exclamation mark for breaking changes).
- Body should explain motivation and context; reference issues when applicable.
- Footer for breaking changes: `BREAKING CHANGE: ...`.

